p: Crude endophytic extract of Enterobacter asburiae, Pseudomonas sp., Arthrobacter pascens, and Pseudomonas palleroniana displayed no noteworthy activity against UMG87 glioblastoma cells and A549 lung carcinoma cells. The extracts can be tested on other cancer cell lines to determine their activity. Pseudomonas sp. are known to produce anticancer compounds and have been reported to have activity against a number of human cancer cell lines [ 86, 87]. Pseudomonas sp. and Pseudomonas cichorii displayed no noteworthy activity against UMG87 glioblastoma cells and A549 lung carcinoma cells. Pseudomonas palleroniana crude extracts displayed 36% cell reduction at 100 μg/mL against A549 lung carcinoma cells.
